    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Thanks for the clear answers.\r\n\r\nHere is snippet of my `infobox`, I am not sure it is the right way but it does work, if it can help someone.\r\n\r\n```js\r\n<!-- require infobox.js -->\r\n\r\nvar search = instantsearch({\r\n  appId: xxx,\r\n  apiKey: xxx,\r\n  indexName: xxx\r\n});\r\n\r\nvar o = new InfoBox({/*options*/});\r\n\r\nvar map = instantsearch.widgets.geoSearch({\r\n  container: '#map',\r\n  googleReference: window.google,\r\n  customHTMLMarker: {\r\n    template:  function(e) {\r\n      return '<div>' + e.title + '</div>'\r\n    },\r\n    events: {\r\n      click: function(e) {\r\n        o.getMap() && o.close(), o.setContent('<div>' + e.item.title + '</div>'), o.open(e.map, e.marker)\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  },\r\n});\r\n\r\nsearch.addWidget(map);\r\nsearch.start();\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n**Question about Places with GeoSearch:**\r\nI am now trying to display an _Algolia Places_ [search input](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/dev-novel/?selectedStory=GeoSearch.with%20position%20from%20Places) to my `geoSearch` widget. I gathered that the _Places_ script is already included in `instantsearch.js`, so I don't need to reference it.\r\n\r\nBut I am having hard times to understand how to implement it, could someone give me a simple example? \r\n\r\n_It could be nice if the [examples](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/dev-novel) had a little snippet to copy._",
