    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> It could be nice if the [examples](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/dev-novel) had a little snippet to copy.\r\n\r\nYes, you are right we should provide some links & snippets for the examples. Thanks for your feedback! For now you can find all the examples on GitHub. Here is [the code](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/develop/dev/app/builtin/stories/geo-search.stories.js) for the examples about the GeoSearch widget.\r\n\r\n> **Question about Places with GeoSearch:**\r\nI am now trying to display an _Algolia Places_ [search input](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/dev-novel/?selectedStory=GeoSearch.with%20position%20from%20Places) to my `geoSearch` widget. I gathered that the _Places_ script is already included in `instantsearch.js`, so I don't need to reference it.\r\n>\r\n>But I am having hard times to understand how to implement it, could someone give me a simple example? \r\n\r\nActually no Places is not provided with InstantSearch. You need to install it on your own and then use the widget shipped with the library to use it with InstantSearch. You can find more informations about how to use it & integrate it in [the Places documentation](https://community.algolia.com/places/examples.html#instantsearchjs). Here is [the lines](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/develop/dev/app/builtin/stories/geo-search.stories.js#L197-L232) that create the Places example with the GeoSearch widget.",
