    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "@samouss -- Algolia is great and we're paying a ton of money for it. So, I don't think it's too much to ask to have comprehensive examples all in one place with code snippets. The documentation is literally and figuratively all over the place. I'm trying to figure out how to add a geo search map to my site, and the example you provided above doesn't really fit the need. I looked on this page (https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/widgets/geoSearch.html), but the example is minimal and produces this error: \"instantsearch.widgets.geoSearch is not a function\". I'm honestly growing tired of trying to unravel other people's code just to get stuff done.\r\n\r\nAny ideas of where I could find good examples, and why the code snippet from the widgets page does not work?",
