    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@vaughn-taylor I'm sorry that you have some issue with the GeoSearch widget. First of all thanks for your feedback, indeed you are right we should have code snippets or a guide that demonstrate the usage of the widget. All the sources of the examples in [our widget showcase](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/dev-novel/?selectedStory=GeoSearch.default) are available on [GitHub](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/develop/dev/app/builtin/stories/geo-search.stories.js#L75-L81), we know that it's not the best place for discoverability but for now it's the solution that we have. \r\n\r\nAbout the error, you need to have the latest version ([v2.6.0](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/blob/develop/CHANGELOG.md#260-2018-03-06)) of InstantSearch in order to have the widget available. If the problem persist you can do a small example, I'll be happy to help you implement the widget. We have a template available for the example to avoid your all the boilerplate part. You can find it on [CodeSandbox](https://codesandbox.io/s/github/algolia/instantsearch-templates/tree/master/src/InstantSearch.js).",
