  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@samouss a simple use case is getting the geolocation from the user's device and doing a map center based on it. e.g. even a simple `map.setCenter({lat: -34, lng: 151});` isn't possible with the current setup.\r\n\r\nTwo other use cases:\r\n1) Full control over the Places.js integration: it could function as a \"zoom to location\" from a map that starts out fully zoomed out (addressing this pull request: https://github.com/algolia/places/pull/554). It would also allow you to process a search like \"xyz near me\".\r\n\r\n2) Saving the map bounds (via event listener `bounds_changed` on map) to the URL hash and then reading those values via the event listener `idle` state so you can share a page with exact search results.",
    "created_at": "2018-08-08T21:05:53Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/2778#issuecomment-411552188",
    "id": 411552188,
