  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "For the first use case you can fetch the position from the device then mount the widget with the retrieved position. For the last use case we have already have [an issue opened](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/issues/2876) about the routing implementation. But I completely agree with you it could be handy to provide an access to the map instance (probably through an event). I've opened [an issue](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch.js/issues/3059) about that.\r\n\r\nFor the moment a possible solution is to re-implement your own widget with [the connector API](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/guides/customization.html). This API lets you have full control on the rendering. You can use the [`connectGeoSearch`](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/connectors/connectGeoSearch.html) connector to implement the widget.",
